            <creation>This story, with the short title "Nobles Devoted to the Miracles of Mary Book," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1850</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>After hearing about a miracle performed by Mary, half the aristocrats in a town became monks. The other half grew envious and went to stone the monks. However, Mary safeguarded the monks by hiding them, and this miracle convinced the holdouts to put their faith in Mary.</p>
